  "texts": [
    "While this loss is not as well-motivated as torsional losses proposed by ref.",
    "56, we find that it achieves strong empirical results.",
    "L w = 0:5 We normalize all angles in the training set to be zero mean by subtracting their element-wise angular mean μ; validation and test sets are shifted by this same offset.",
    "Figure 1 illustrates this overall training process, including our previously described internal angle framing.",
    "The internal angles describing the folded chain x 0 are corrupted until they become indistinguishable from random angles, which results in a disordered mass of residues at x T; we sample points along this diffusion process to train our model nn ξ."
